Here is the bubble sort code in Python:
```python
def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
    return arr
print(bubble_sort([64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90]))
```

Here is the bubble sort code in JavaScript:
```javascript
function bubbleSort(arr) {
  let n = arr.length;
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    for (let j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {
      if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
        [arr[j], arr[j + 1]] = [arr[j + 1], arr[j]];
      }
    }
  }
  return arr;
}
console.log(bubbleSort([64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90]));
```

